ng a new topic.";i:42;s:89:"The postures serve as an inspiration guide but please encourage the childrens creativity.";i:43;s:50:"Find all these chair yoga poses in our Chair Yoga.";i:44;s:201:"Exercise 4 Chair Marching First check your posture Lift alternate legs so that your feet lift about 2 inches from the floor and swing your arms forwards and back at a speed that is comfortable for you.";i:45;s:43:"Imagine you marching along at a brisk pace.";i:46;s:85:"Continue for about 20 30 seconds Benefits Improves circulation and warms the muscles.";i:47;s:22:"Sit tall in the chair.";i:48;s:101:"Place put your left hand on the seat behind you and your right hand on the outside of your left knee.";i:49;s:61:"Inhale and reach your head up with energy toward the ceiling.";i:50;s:53:"As you exhale gently turn your shoulders to the left.";i:51;s:78:"To help deepen your twist gently press your left hand against your right knee.";i:52;s:86:"Chair yoga modifies asanas at your seat and can deliver the poses to a wider audience.";i:53;s:167:"It can be practiced in the office when you need a mid-day boost help seniors stay mobile and social offer alternatives for injuries and introduce yoga to the disabled.";i:54;s:27:"The Benefits of Chair Yoga.";i:55;s:29:"Opens the hips and shoulders.";i:56;s:102:"Chair yoga refers to yoga practices that can be done while sitting in a chair or using it for support.";i:57;s:60:"Read this article to discover 8 awesome chair yoga postures.";i:58;s:121:"Yoga is a low-impact form of exercise that helps the body stretch to improve flexibility circulation and range of motion.";i:59;s:25:"Chair Exercises for Legs.";i:60;s:89:"It may seem impossible to strengthen your legs while sitting down but you absolutely can.";i:61;s:77:"Here are a few chair exercises for legs to work your quads glutes and calves.";i:62;s:50:"Sit up straight with your feet flat on the ground.";i:63;s:83:"The Chair Pose is a yoga exercise that works the butt thighs hamstrings and calves.";i:64;s:38:"It works your body similar to a squat.";i:65;s:52:"Sit as far back as you are comfortable in this pose.";i:66;s:86:"Your aim is to get to the point where you can make a 90 degree angle out of your legs.";i:67;s:80:"It will take awhile before you can do that in chair pose but the point is to go.";i:68;s:57:"Sit straight in the chair with your legs in front of you.";i:69;s:45:"Now turn to the side and sit facing the left.";i:70;s:118:"Now go through these warrior poses with your arms to the ceiling while on the left then turn and do them to the right.";i:71;s:104:"Keep your right leg to the side of the chair but take your left leg and swing it to the backside of you.";}}